## **Layer 2: Derived Metrics (The Hidden Math)**

These calculations happen behind the scenes and are NOT displayed directly to users, but feed into Layer 3 outputs.

### **A. Growth Mechanics**

javascript  
*// 1\. Adjusted Target Revenue (if sliders used)*  
const adjusted\_target\_revenue \= target\_revenue \* (1 \+ growth\_adjustment\_pct);

*// 2\. Revenue Gap*  
const revenue\_gap \= adjusted\_target\_revenue \- baseline\_revenue;

*// 3\. Required CAGR*  
const timeframe\_years \= target\_timeframe\_months / 12;

const required\_cagr \= Math.pow(adjusted\_target\_revenue / baseline\_revenue, 1 / timeframe\_years) \- 1;

---

### **B. Retention & Churn Math (NEW in V2)**

javascript  
*// 4\. Adjusted Retention Rate (if slider used)*  
const adjusted\_retention\_rate \= Math.min(0.99, Math.max(0.50,   
  baseline\_retention\_rate \+ retention\_adjustment\_pct  
));

*// 5\. Annual Churn Rate*  
const annual\_churn\_rate \= 1 \- adjusted\_retention\_rate;

*// 6\. Churn Replacement Revenue (Total over timeframe)*  
*// This is the revenue that will churn during the growth period*  
const churn\_replacement\_revenue \= baseline\_revenue \* annual\_churn\_rate \* timeframe\_years;

*// 7\. Total Sales Revenue Needed*  
*// This is the TRUE amount of revenue that must be sold*  
const total\_sales\_revenue\_needed \= revenue\_gap \+ churn\_replacement\_revenue;

*// 8\. Churn Replacement Percentage (KEY PRESSURE INDICATOR)*

const churn\_replacement\_pct \= churn\_replacement\_revenue / total\_sales\_revenue\_needed;

**Example:**

* Current Revenue: $2M  
* Target Revenue: $3M (in 2 years)  
* Retention: 85% (so 15% annual churn)  
* Revenue Gap: $1M  
* Churn Replacement: $2M × 0.15 × 2 years \= $600K  
* Total Sales Needed: $1M \+ $600K \= $1.6M  
* Churn Replacement %: $600K / $1.6M \= **37.5%**

**Insight:** "You need to sell $1.6M to grow $1M—37.5% of your effort is just replacing churn."

