### **C. Client & Sales Velocity Math (NEW in V2)**

javascript  
*// 9\. Adjusted ACV (if slider used)*  
const adjusted\_acv \= baseline\_acv \* (1 \+ acv\_adjustment\_pct);

*// 10\. Current Client Count at Baseline*  
*// Already have baseline\_client\_count*

*// 11\. Target Client Count*  
const target\_client\_count \= adjusted\_target\_revenue / adjusted\_acv;

*// 12\. Net New Clients Needed*  
const net\_new\_clients\_needed \= target\_client\_count \- baseline\_client\_count;

*// 13\. Clients Churned During Period*  
const clients\_churned \= baseline\_client\_count \* annual\_churn\_rate \* timeframe\_years;

*// 14\. Gross Sales Wins Required*  
*// Must replace churned clients AND add net new*  
const gross\_sales\_wins\_required \= net\_new\_clients\_needed \+ clients\_churned;

*// 15\. Monthly Sales Velocity Required*  
const monthly\_sales\_velocity\_required \= gross\_sales\_wins\_required / target\_timeframe\_months;

*// 16\. Current Sales Velocity (if available from Snapshot)*  
*// This would come from Agency Snapshot: new\_clients\_this\_month*  
const current\_monthly\_sales\_velocity \= baseline\_client\_count \* (1 / 12); *// Proxy if not available*

*// 17\. Sales Velocity Multiplier (KEY PRESSURE INDICATOR)*

const sales\_velocity\_multiplier \= monthly\_sales\_velocity\_required / current\_monthly\_sales\_velocity;

**Example:**

* Revenue Gap: $1M  
* Adjusted ACV: $50K (if user raised prices \+25%)  
* Net New Clients: $1M / $50K \= 20 clients  
* Clients Churned: 30 clients × 0.15 × 2 years \= 9 clients  
* Gross Sales Wins: 20 \+ 9 \= 29 deals  
* Monthly Velocity: 29 / 24 months \= **1.2 deals/month**  
* Current Velocity: \~1 deal/month  
* Multiplier: **1.2x current pace**

