### **D. Capacity & Headcount Math (NEW in V2)**

javascript  
*// 18\. Adjusted Efficiency (AGI per FTE)*  
const adjusted\_agi\_per\_fte \= baseline\_agi\_per\_fte \* (1 \+ efficiency\_adjustment\_pct);

*// 19\. Target Team Size (Sustainable Headcount)*  
const target\_team\_size \= adjusted\_target\_revenue / adjusted\_agi\_per\_fte;

*// 20\. Headcount Delta*  
const headcount\_delta \= target\_team\_size \- baseline\_team\_size;

*// 21\. Timeframe in Quarters*  
const timeframe\_quarters \= target\_timeframe\_months / 3;

*// 22\. Hiring Pace (Hires Per Quarter) \- KEY PRESSURE INDICATOR*  
const hiring\_pace\_per\_quarter \= headcount\_delta / timeframe\_quarters;

*// 23\. Hiring Velocity as % of Current Team*  
const hiring\_velocity\_pct \= hiring\_pace\_per\_quarter / baseline\_team\_size;

*// 24\. Implied AGI per FTE if NO Hiring (Burnout Check)*  
*// What if they miss hiring targets and try to grow with current team?*

const implied\_agi\_per\_fte\_no\_hiring \= adjusted\_target\_revenue / baseline\_team\_size;

**Example:**

* Target Revenue: $3M  
* Adjusted Efficiency: $200K per FTE (if user improved processes \+10%)  
* Target Team Size: $3M / $200K \= 15 FTEs  
* Current Team: 10 FTEs  
* Headcount Delta: 5 new hires  
* Timeframe: 2 years \= 8 quarters  
* Hiring Pace: 5 / 8 \= **0.625 hires per quarter**  
* Hiring Velocity: 0.625 / 10 \= **6.25% per quarter** (safe)

**BUT if they don't hire:**

* Implied AGI/FTE: $3M / 10 \= **$300K per FTE** (danger zone)

