### **E. Economic & Profit Math (NEW in V2)**

javascript  
*// 25\. Adjusted Profit Margin*  
const adjusted\_profit\_margin \= Math.min(0.50, Math.max(0.05,  
  baseline\_profit\_margin \+ margin\_adjustment\_pct  
));

*// 26\. Baseline Profit Pool ($)*  
const baseline\_profit \= baseline\_revenue \* baseline\_profit\_margin;

*// 27\. Target Profit Pool ($)*  
const target\_profit \= adjusted\_target\_revenue \* adjusted\_profit\_margin;

*// 28\. Profit Delta*  
const profit\_delta \= target\_profit \- baseline\_profit;

*// 29\. Implied New Payroll Cost (Using 45% rule)*  
*// New AGI \= Revenue Gap (assuming 90% AGI margin)*  
const new\_agi \= revenue\_gap \* 0.90;  
const implied\_new\_payroll \= new\_agi \* 0.45;

*// 30\. Monthly New Payroll Burn*  
const monthly\_new\_payroll\_burn \= implied\_new\_payroll / 12;

*// 31\. Monthly Baseline Profit*  
const monthly\_baseline\_profit \= baseline\_profit / 12;

*// 32\. Cash Flow Pinch Check (KEY PRESSURE INDICATOR)*  
*// Can current profit cover new payroll before revenue catches up?*

const cash\_flow\_coverage\_ratio \= monthly\_baseline\_profit / monthly\_new\_payroll\_burn;

**Example:**

* Revenue Gap: $1M  
* New AGI: $1M × 0.90 \= $900K  
* Implied New Payroll: $900K × 0.45 \= **$405K/year** ($34K/month)  
* Current Monthly Profit: $300K / 12 \= $25K/month  
* Coverage Ratio: $25K / $34K \= **0.73** (not enough cash flow\!)

**Insight:** "Your current monthly profit only covers 73% of the new payroll burn. You'll need reserves or front-load cash to fund growth."

