*// \========================================*  
*// 2\. ACV Rate of Change (Pace Signal)*  
*// \========================================*

*// Annualized ACV growth rate (CAGR-style)*  
const acv\_annual\_growth\_rate \= Math.pow(  
  adjusted\_acv / baseline\_acv,   
  1 / timeframe\_years

) \- 1;

**Example:**

* Baseline ACV: $24K  
* Adjusted ACV: $36K  
* Timeframe: 18 months (1.5 years)  
* `acv_annual_growth_rate`: (36K/24K)^(1/1.5) \- 1 \= **0.291** (29.1% annually)

**Interpretation (revised):** "Value capture per client must increase by \~29% annually. This pace indicates monetization changes need to happen during execution, not as a one-time adjustment before growth begins."

