javascript  
*// \========================================*  
*// 3\. ACV Dependency Ratio (Structural Reliance Signal)*  
*// \========================================*

*// Total revenue growth*  
const total\_revenue\_growth \= adjusted\_target\_revenue \- baseline\_revenue;

*// Revenue growth from ACV change alone (holding client count constant)*  
const growth\_from\_acv\_only \= baseline\_client\_count \* (adjusted\_acv \- baseline\_acv);

*// Revenue growth from volume change alone (holding ACV constant)*  
const growth\_from\_volume\_only \= (target\_client\_count \- baseline\_client\_count) \* baseline\_acv;

*// Cross-effect (both changing together)*  
const growth\_cross\_effect \= (target\_client\_count \- baseline\_client\_count) \* (adjusted\_acv \- baseline\_acv);

*// ACV Dependency Ratio ⭐ PRIMARY PRESSURE INDICATOR*

const acv\_dependency\_ratio \= growth\_from\_acv\_only / total\_revenue\_growth;

**Example:**

* Baseline: $2M revenue, 80 clients, $25K ACV  
* Target: $3M revenue, 90 clients, $33.3K ACV  
* Total Growth: $1M  
* Growth from ACV only: 80 × ($33.3K \- $25K) \= **$664K**  
* Growth from volume only: 10 × $25K \= **$250K**  
* `acv_dependency_ratio`: $664K / $1M \= **0.664 (66.4%)**

**Interpretation (revised):** "66% of your revenue growth comes from extracting more value per existing client relationship scale, rather than from adding new clients. The plan has limited volume-based fallback options if monetization improvements don't materialize."

