### **⚖️ Trade-Off Alert (Scenario Comparison)**

This only fires when comparing 2+ scenarios. It identifies which dimension differs most between scenarios.

javascript  
function calculateTradeOffAlert(scenarioA, scenarioB) {  
  const deltas \= {  
    headcount: Math.abs(scenarioA.headcount\_delta \- scenarioB.headcount\_delta),  
    sales\_velocity: Math.abs(scenarioA.monthly\_velocity \- scenarioB.monthly\_velocity),  
    profit: Math.abs(scenarioA.profit\_delta \- scenarioB.profit\_delta),  
    client\_complexity: Math.abs(scenarioA.target\_client\_count \- scenarioB.target\_client\_count)  
  };  
    
  const max\_delta \= Math.max(...Object.values(deltas));  
  const primary\_trade\_off \= Object.keys(deltas).find(key \=\> deltas\[key\] \=== max\_delta);  
    
  *// Return trade-off summary*  
  if (primary\_trade\_off \=== 'headcount') {  
    return {  
      label: "Efficiency vs. Volume Trade-Off",  
      message: "Scenario A requires more headcount; Scenario B achieves similar revenue with fewer people"  
    };  
  }  
  *// ... similar logic for other trade-offs*

}

